# Multi-Region Boundaries

- Region is chosen at deploy time through `SITE_REGION` / `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_REGION`. Do not infer region from request host unless the user explicitly asks for host-based multi-tenancy.
- Keep branching at boundaries such as region helpers, provider registries, config maps, or router registration. Avoid scattering `if region == ...` / `region === ...` through shared business logic.
- When changing auth, payment, pricing, i18n, SEO, CORS, OAuth callback URLs, or analytics, verify behavior for both `cn` and `global`.
- Shared pages should stay data-driven. Prefer `src/lib/region.ts`, `src/lib/pricing.ts`, and provider registries over duplicating whole pages or components.
- Do not let frontend-only region changes drift from backend behavior. Callback URLs, webhook endpoints, legal copy, and metadata must stay aligned with the selected deployment.
